{
  "info": {
    "name": "AMS – Asset Management System",
    "_postman_id": "ams-hexaware-collection",
    "description": "Complete API collection for AMS Capstone Project (Hexaware).\n\n🔐 HOW TO USE:\n1. Run '01. Register Employee' first to create an account\n2. Run '03. Login as Employee' → copy the token from the response\n3. Click the collection name → Variables → paste token in emp_token\n4. Run '04. Login as Admin' (admin/admin123) → paste token in admin_token\n5. All other requests will work automatically using those tokens\n\nBase URL: http://localhost:8080\n\n📦 v2 CATEGORY APIS (added):\n- GET /api/v2/categories/all-with-count → ADMIN only\n- GET /api/v2/categories/search?name={keyword} → any authenticated user\n- GET /api/v2/categories/get/{id} → any authenticated user",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "01. Register Employee (Public)",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"john.doe\",\n  \"password\": \"john@123\",\n  \"role\": \"EMPLOYEE\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "http://localhost:8080/api/users/add",
          "host": [
            "http://localhost:8080"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "users",
            "add"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Register a new employee account. This endpoint is public — no token needed.\n\nExpected Response: 200 OK with UserRespDto (id, username, role, createdAt)"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "02. Register Admin (Public)",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"admin\",\n  \"password\": \"admin@123\",\n  \"role\": \"ADMIN\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "http://localhost:8080/api/users/add",
          "host": [
            "http://localhost:8080"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "users",
            "add"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Register an admin account. Public endpoint — no token needed.\n\nExpected Response: 200 OK with UserRespDto"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "03. Login as Employee → Get JWT Token",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": ""
        },
        "auth": {
          "type": "basic",
          "basic": [
            {
              "key": "username",
              "value": "john.doe"
            },
            {
              "key": "password",
              "value": "john@123"
            }
          ]
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login",
          "host": [
            "http://localhost:8080"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "auth",
            "login"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Login using Basic Auth (username + password).\n\nSpring Security verifies credentials → generates JWT token.\n\n✅ AFTER RUNNING:\nCopy the 'token' value from the response → paste it in Collection Variables → emp_token\n\nExpected Response:\n{\n  \"username\": \"john.doe\",\n  \"token\": \"eyJhbGciO...\"\n}"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "04. Login as Admin → Get JWT Token",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": ""
        },
        "auth": {
          "type": "basic",
          "basic": [
            {
              "key": "username",
              "value": "admin"
            },
            {
              "key": "password",
              "value": "admin@123"
            }
          ]
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login",
          "host": [
            "http://localhost:8080"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "auth",
            "login"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Login as admin using Basic Auth.\n\n✅ AFTER RUNNING:\nCopy the 'token' value from response → paste in Collection Variables → admin_token\n\nExpected Response:\n{\n  \"username\": \"admin\",\n  \"token\": \"eyJhbGciO...\"\n}"
      }
    },
    {
